items.name: Sagat (Street Fighter FanArt Based) + Deliner [Dual LORA]
items.description:
Hello!

Welcome to one of my weirdest experiments I have ever done. Dual LORA [Character+Splitted Style].

But, this wasn't Sagat from Street fighter? Yes and no.

Short story, this LORA was not trained under normal circumstances and it can be used to create Sagat in a very specific style on a lot of models and use that line style to apply on any other concepts but using Lykon's AnyLora (primary).

So... why not a normal LORA?
********************************
Cause if you put just one Sagat image with his eyepatch (captioned or not), it blows the face and the body in the training and the inferencing. Tried 15 trainings this week, nothing.

What I did? Hands at work in Photoshop (time without drawing lol) and created several illustration and trained from there, I have added a pureref chart in the end of images to explain this best. Basically I had to draw, again (and using AI on my advance to speed up this), lol. This way I get cleaner images to train and without his eyepatch. The scar is other story and it reflects it more or less depending on the LORA's strength.

That's why in the training it got my lining style (splitted training) plus the character. So we can say this is an stylization or a fan art (and I'm not gonna do this anymore except when the AI's internal understanding limits the trainings).


Token is Sagat and for the style just not use Sagat and drop to 0.7 (recommended) the strength, Prompt anything you want. Easy.

Recommendations
*********************

- Models to inference: If you just want Sagat you can use several (AnyLora, RevAnimated, Colorful..) but if you want just the style is extremely recommended and I can't say this will work in other models (cause maybe conflicts), Anylora.

- Strenghts: 0.8-1 for Sagat prompting and 0.6-0.7 for style in AnyLora.

This LORA is good for:
************************
- Sagat half body, fullbody, action poses and very low profile portraits.
- It can do backgrounds till a certain level, if you feel like you're not getting them drop Sagat from 1 to 0.7/0.8.
- Anime/manga/lineart and some semi realistic/concept styles depending on models.
- Lineart style punching the contrast (under the circumstances of AnyLora explained above).


Sorry for messing so much this time and hope you don't find this extremely complex.
Thanks to Lykon for the Anylora's, didn't know it was so powerful when training (specially different images).

Feel free to support us at:
https://www.patreon.com/user?u=90661954

Thanks to all!

items.name: [Character] Narmaya / MultiVerCostume (Granblue Fantasy) LoRa/LoCon/LoHa
items.description:
Reference from Granblue Fantasy Character, Narmaya.

This Model is to achieve Narmaya Multi Version Costume that close to replicate her multiple attire in Granblue Fantasy with just 1 model by using specific trigger word, "ver1costume~ver8costume".

Summary about this model:
-Multi Version Costume are close represent of her Ingame variety attire
-Work on weight 1 to go
-Volatile, any of costume may mix up
-some checkpoint may end up less details
-ver1 and ver2 Costume highly volatile/easily mix due to similarities of both design.

===========================================================
How to use Lora:
LoRa:
-download the LoRa Model
-move this data into your Stable Diffusion -> Models -> Lora

LoCon & LoHa (LyCoris):
-Make sure your SD already contains LyCoris Extension https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-lycoris
-download the LoCon or LoHa models
-Move the data into your Stable Diffusion -> Models -> Lycoris

===========================================================

Trigger Words Simplify:
Default: ``1girl, narmaya \(granblue fantasy\), draph``
Optional: ``ver1costume~ver8costume`` and ``narunsfw``


Each of VerCostume Trigger will require ":1.2" regardless due to amount of different costume version and database been applied and current costume is easily volatile or mixing.
To prompt 1 of 8 VerCostume, below is an example:

Yukata Version:
``Yukata, (ver6costume:1.2), 1girl, narmaya \(granblue fantasy\), draph, <lora:NarmayaLoRa:1>``


Xmas Version:
``Xmas, (ver7costume:1.2), 1girl, narmaya \(granblue fantasy\), draph, <lora:NarmayaLoRa:1>``

Yukata Version:
``Butterfly, (ver5costume:1.2), 1girl, narmaya \(granblue fantasy\), draph, <lora:NarmayaLoRa:1>``

Maid Version:
``Maid, (ver8costume:1.2), 1girl, narmaya \(granblue fantasy\), draph, <lora:NarmayaLoRa:1>``



Non-VerCostume Trigger Words:
Other Costume that may have nothing to do with her ingame variation are also possible by only just use ``1girl, narmaya \(granblue fantasy\), draph, <lora:NarmayaLoRa:1>``. But the costume may reflect the same design among vercostume.



During self testing, it is found that certain VerCostume is unstable or over mixing which will be ver1costume and ver2costume since both sharing close to same attire but different layer clothes. This issues may resolve by next version.
===========================================================

This is my first time trying to get multiple unique attire of 1 character in 1 Model instead of describe every of their attire or outright does not replicate the same design. I be very apricate to get Feedback since I'm still continue self learning Lora Training.

If anyone wish to ask anything personally, directly contact or find me via CivitAI Discord by same user name, deatharms2010.

Cheers~

items.description:
This is a LoRA for the character Emma, from Hentai University a game by Noodle Jacuzzi. And this time, it's actually a character I wrote in the game.

Amy's art is from the artist Himitsu Kessha Vanitas, the sets -

Q. Bushitsu o Kitsuenjo Gawari ni Shiteiru Yankee ni Yarasete Ageyouka to Iwaretara ? A. Nanyakanya de Haramaseru

Rinjin no Yankee Onna to SeFrie ni Natta Hanashi

I've been working my way through making these for all the characters currently in the game, and sharing them in the Discord for HU, but figured I should also put them up here.

In general, I'm working from pretty limited image sets, so expect the results to be a bit wonky at times.

I recommend a weight of around 0.5, possibly lower depending if you're combining the character LoRA with other styles/costumes/etc. along with tagging some defining characteristics of the character you're generating. Higher than that can really push the artist's original style, and may cause you issues.

All characters I train have a "character tag" added into the set to help generate them fairly reliably.

Recommended LoRA Weight - 0.5 for fairly flexible, higher if you want more of the original artist's style, lower if it doesn't play nice with other loras.

Character tag - HUAmy
Recommended tags - blonde hair, long hair, braid, green or yellow eyes, large breasts,

I may have forgotten to check and tag eye color when doing my testing, but hey. If you want it to be "set accurate" be sure to tag.

I've got quite a backlog of these made up already, so I'll be uploading them on and off.

Check my other uploads as I put them out for more HU characters, and if you want any specific character put up soon, let me know.

items.name: Lora Lover (Realistic)
items.description:
So this is a model that I combined from a few others surrounding the photorealistic premise. In the beginning it was just me trying to get a better photorealistic model, but I ended up finding that it has a special niche that I think it does really well in the realistic category.

If you are training your own lora of a character, person, or celebrity, this model tends to accept the lora into it very well. The model you train it with matters a bit, but I was able to get better results with this model when using loras trained on a specific person than the other popular realistic models out there.

It can definitely take a lot of tweaking and fine tuning when using a lora with a model so give it some practice and hopefully you will get some results.

items.name: Bryce Dallas Howard
items.description: Bryce Dallas Howard was lacking in the various models so I made a Lora. I recommend against restore faces as it makes it a generic person at the last minute. And I recommend creating your image using the lora to get a generic likeness and composition and then inpainting her face again, setting to Only Masked 512x512 and set the denoising strength to 0.4 or higher. This will make it look much more like her. But test to see what works for you. Name her 'BryceDHoward' in your prompt along with the Lora for best results before inpainting with the lora again. She has crazy green eyes in real life, so test inpainting her eyes after inpainting her face as the AI gets confused by her eyes. Not always necessary but helps if you get weird eyes.

items.name: Usagi Tsukino (Fanart) - Sailor Moon (LOCON version)
items.description:
Note: This was trained mostly on Kuroinuu Juu and Glamour works so it has a bias towards bigger breasts. Don't complain if you try to make her flat and it doesn't work.

V2:

Here's the V2 as promised, a bit late because there was a power outage minutes before saving the last epoch. Was the universe against it? Likely! But as a deviant proud man of culture, the universe can go fuck self pleasure itself :P.

Works fine with: <lora:SMUsagiTsukinoV16:0.65> smusagitsukino, <outfit>

I managed to more or less isolate the following outfits, I had to be stupidly specific to maximize separation as i kept getting a virtual soup:

  • ClassicSM_Blue_skirt_White_gloves_Red_boots_Red_choker_Red_bowtie_Red_back_bow_Circlet_Red_bun_cover

  • EternalSM_Yellow_layered_skirt_Pink_puffy_sleeves_White_gloves_White_boots_Wing_brooch_Red_choker_Red_ribbon_Wings_Hairpin_Red_bun_cover_Golden_crescent_forehead_mark

  • SuperSM_White_skirt_White_gloves_Red_boots_Yellow_choker_Red_bowtie_White_back_bow_Crescent_circlet_Hairpin_Red_bun_cover

  • Princess_white_strapless_dress_huge_back_bow_Golden_crescent_forehead_mark

  • school_uniform_blue_serafuku_blue_back_bow_red_bowtie

  • golden_crescent_forehead_mark: use this in the negatives to get rid of it or boost it.

This V2 is technically V16 while the prodigy optimizer is not normally better than AdamW. In some edge case like this where the sailor moon concept is so cooked into the model it overbakes anything even tangentially related to it.

So here's what happened, the eternal outfit is much more complex that the other ones yet is still recognized by SD as a sailor senshi outfit. So to train it properly I need to increase the repetitions but the sailor moon concept is so trained into the model that the extra repetitions overbaked the LORA. The V1 iteration of the LOCON was done using normalization to limit the over bakedness but it only worked to a point. I spent most of this and the past week tweaking the repetitions, tagging and leaning rate, until i stumbled on the Prodigy optimizer. As it is dynamic it seems to have done a good job at leaning the undertrained parts(the outfits) while ignoring the over trained parts(usagi herself.)

Regardless! As always I'll add the training dataset and tags summary so people can play with those. There's a lot of bits and pieces of her uniform in there if you want to mix and match instead of only using her stock uniform.

V1:

Don't you have one of those occasions in which you know the answer to a problem, you actually have two plausible solutions and yet you stupidly take the third, the long shot one?

Well this is it. This LOCON uses mostly the same dataset as my LORA version with some minor tweaking.

Seems to work fine with: <lyco:SMUsagiTsukinoV6:.6>, SMUsagiTsukino,

Available clothing sets are:

  • StandardSenshiOutfit

  • EternalSMOutfit (Bleeds over super)

  • SuperSMOutfit (Bleeds over Eternal)

  • SMPrincessOutfit

  • SMSchoolUniform

  • KuroInuLingerieSailorOutfit (porny)

Note: This is not better than the LORA, it is just different. Only "positive" thing I noticed is that If you use it with a photorealistic model, it makes dollar store cosplayers.

The issue with my LORA was bleeding between costumes, it is till present here but in a lesser degree. My plausible solutions were either isolate the costumes as if the were different characters essentially making the LORA a character pack or B use regularization images to make sure the LORA understood that Usagi Tsukino isn't the same as sailor moon. Well I choose the third option, my thought process went like this: "LOCON absorb more detail, thus even if LORA sees them as the same maybe the LOCON won't" and it kind of worked. Her default outfit and the Kuroinu's porny one have a lot less bleeding. Super and eternal are sill a soup. I blame the skirts multi color nature making them absurdly similar tag wise in SD's eyes making them essentially the same except for some coloring and small accessories.

Anyway... at some point I'll do a retrain, probably isolating the outfits as individual characters, if I have the motivation i might even do a V2 for both the LORA and the LOCON. I could try reg images but the extra training time coupled with my inexperience makes me reluctant. The theory seems sound in my mind, in fact i already had a small group of images tagged only as Usagi tsukino and expected SD to sort the tags by itself, but they were a relatively small amount of images compared to the full weight of the others, if I use them as Reg images I'll have to up the repetitions by a lot. and probably double the already long training time. But I am rambling let's leave it as regularization images seem like a solution but they always bite at your available training time.

As always I'll add the training dataset and tags summary so people can play with those.
